        <AnnotationLayout
          Text="Variable Need to Change:&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;****************************** _TableReference_Id ***************************************&#xA;Use: &#xA;_TableReference_Id =  This is &quot;REQUIRED&quot;, used in getting data for source and destination.&#xA;Used in all Phase.&#xA;Sample Value:&#xA;_TableReference_Id = &quot;100001&quot;&#xA;&#xA;******************************_AdditionalQueryFilter ************************************&#xA;Use: &#xA;_AdditionalQueryFilter =  This is &quot;NOT-REQUEIRED&quot; only case to case bases. Note that always&#xA;put an &quot;AND&quot; first before the query.&#xA;Used in all Transformation Phase.&#xA;&#xA;Sample Value:&#xA;_AdditionalQueryFilter = &quot;AND query*&quot;&#xA;&#xA;****************************** _MonthInterval_Query ************************************&#xA;Use:&#xA;_MonthInterval_Query = This is for the interval once the Package is &quot;Deployed&quot;. Empty this&#xA;variable of you want to Load all data and add the value if you need a specific range of data &#xA;set needed to be updated. &#xA;Used in Tansformation Phase.&#xA;Example last 3 months&#xA;&#xA;&quot;+@[User::SourceDate_Reference]+&quot; &gt; DATE_ADD(CURRENT_DATE(), INTERVAL -3 MONTH)&#xA;&#xA;Sample Value:&#xA;_MonthInterval_Query  = &quot;DATE_ADD(CURRENT_DATE(), INTERVAL -3 MONTH)&quot; &#xA;&#xA;Note:&#xA;&#xA;For Master Data you can use select *&#xA;but for table header and details &#xA;use manual query (for null date)&#xA;&#xA;"
          ParentId="Package"
          FontInfo="{assembly:Null}"
          Size="520,646"
          Id="7f687eb7-0e15-4c85-a452-e77fc7f1cdd7"
          TopLeft="20.3888888888883,90.3333333333337" />
        <AnnotationLayout
          Text="Note :&#xA;AND BPCODE IN (SELECT DISTINCT CODE FROM U_CUSTOMER_DIVISION WHERE U_DIVISION IN ('TABLE EGGS SALES', 'RTL SALES', 'DOP SALES', 'LAYER CULLS SALES'))"
          ParentId="Package"
          FontInfo="{assembly:Null}"
          Size="914,56"
          Id="7c6dbb36-be9d-4fc4-a317-8e9eb030014c"
          TopLeft="1278.88888888889,258.888888888889" />
      </GraphLayout>
    </LayoutInfo>
